{"defendant":"Turkey; Turkish government","defendant_evidence":"Turkey had violated journalist Mehmet Hasan Altan's freedom of expression after continuing to detain him

The Turkish government shut down the news channel and a special prosecutor brought terrorism charges against Mr. Altan","defendant_explanation":"The case before the European Court of Human Rights is brought by Mehmet Hasan Altan alleging violations of his rights by the Turkish state authorities, referred to as Turkey and the Turkish government, which detained and prosecuted him and were ordered to pay damages.","defendant_classification":"government","classification_evidence":"Turkey had violated journalist Mehmet Hasan Altan's freedom of expression

The Turkish government shut down the news channel","classification_explanation":"Turkey and the Turkish government are state authorities acting in an official capacity, so they are classified as government."}

{"defendant":"State of Rhode Island; Commonwealth of Pennsylvania","defendant_evidence":"brought suit against the State of Rhode Island

brought suit against the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania","defendant_explanation":"In each underlying case, citizens and taxpayers sued their respective state governments challenging the constitutionality of state statutes funding religious schools, so the defendants are the State of Rhode Island and the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania.","defendant_classification":"government","classification_evidence":"brought suit against the State of Rhode Island

brought suit against the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania","classification_explanation":"Both Rhode Island and Pennsylvania are state governments being sued in their official capacities over the constitutionality of their statutes, so they are classified as government."}

{"defendant":"U.S. Attorney General; the Government","defendant_evidence":"Mandel's co-Plaintiffs, all university professors, brought action against the Attorney General

The Government appealed.","defendant_explanation":"The professors brought an action challenging the Attorney General’s denial of a visa waiver under the INA; the case is against the U.S. Attorney General, i.e., the Government, which then appealed the injunction.","defendant_classification":"government","classification_evidence":"brought action against the Attorney General

The Government appealed.","classification_explanation":"The Attorney General is a federal government official acting in an official capacity, so the defendant is classified as government."}

{"defendant":"two police departments; the police departments","defendant_evidence":"the refusal of two police departments to disclose to a Hungarian NGO the names of their appointed public defenders

brought an action against the police departments","defendant_explanation":"The underlying domestic action was brought by the Hungarian Helsinki Committee against the police departments that refused to disclose information, and the ECtHR case concerns that refusal, so the police departments are the defendants.","defendant_classification":"government","classification_evidence":"two police departments

the police's appointments of public defence counsel (public defenders)","classification_explanation":"Police departments are state authorities performing public functions, so they are classified as government entities in this case."}
